oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Copy print of Confederate veteran Jefferson Bilbrey and three sons
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Jefferson Bilbrey is standing outside with his three young sons, Luther F., William J. B. and Carl. Bilbrey was a farmer near the Rickman community of Overton County and had served in Co. B, 25th Tenn. Inf. Regt., CSA.; He was mustered in at Livingston on July 30, 1861 and was discharged for disability April 1, 1862 in Mississippi. He married Martha H. "Patsy" Townsend. This photograph was taken after the war.
